{"title":"Storck x PodBike Frikar affordable enclosed e-bike velomobile to replace your car","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/18/storck-x-podbike-frikar-affordable-enclosed-e-bike-velomobile-to-replace-your-car/","date":1634580389000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140026/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_sidewalk-800x480.jpg\" alt=\"PodBike Frikar x Storck enclosed e-bike pedelec e-velomobile\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140026/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_sidewalk-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140026/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_sidewalk-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140026/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_sidewalk-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140026/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_sidewalk-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140026/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_sidewalk-1536x922.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140026/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_sidewalk.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-275168\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>E-bikes are trying to find their way into our hearts on &amp; off-road, but this new 4-wheeled, fully-enclosed Storck x PodBike Frikar e-velomobile just might be a viable solution for some looking to cut back on driving cars. It’s not really an e-bike – this recumbent has four wheels, after all. But it’s at least partly pedal-powered – mixing a bike drivetrain with an e-bike pedelec support. On the plus side, it looks kinda like a cross between a spaceship and a Prius, plus with a totally enclosed cabin, you are protected from the elements so you can ride whatever the weather.</p><h2>Storck x PodBike Frikar enclosed e-bike velomobile</h2><div id=\"attachment_275215\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140021/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_ride-anywhere.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-275215\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140021/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_ride-anywhere.jpg\" alt=\"PodBike Frikar x Storck enclosed e-bike pedelec e-velomobile,&nbsp;headlights\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140021/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_ride-anywhere.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140021/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_ride-anywhere-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140021/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_ride-anywhere-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140021/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_ride-anywhere-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140021/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_ride-anywhere-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140021/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_ride-anywhere-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-275215\">c. Podbike</p></div><p>German bike company Storck and Norwegian micro-mobility start-up Podbike have teamed up to bring their Frikar e-velomobile to a larger market, providing an alternative transportation option for cyclists looking to get out of their cars for short trips. The 4-wheeled, fully-enclosed pedelec is not the first e-velomobile concept we’ve seen from an established bike company, but it looks like it could be one of the most viable solutions. Built on an innovative &amp; simple bike-by-wire system, it also is more affordable than we expected.</p><h3>Tech details</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140017/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_grafitti.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140017/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_grafitti.jpg\" alt=\"PodBike Frikar x Storck enclosed e-bike pedelec e-velomobile,&nbsp;grafitti\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140017/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_grafitti.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140017/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_grafitti-297x167.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140017/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_grafitti-800x450.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140017/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_grafitti-120x68.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140017/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_grafitti-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140017/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_grafitti-1536x864.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The 20″ mag-wheeled Podbike Frikar is 2.36m long x 83.9cm wide x 1.19m tall, making it just a bit wider than a modern enduro bike’s handlebar. Even though it has 4 wheels and a shell, Podbike assures that it is classified as a ‘cycle’ within Europe, letting you ride in cycle lanes without any license or registration (much like the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/09/01/canyon-future-mobility-concept-adds-pedal-assist-electric-car-to-city-e-bike-commute-options/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Canyon Future Mobility</a> concept).</p><p>The 90kg (empty), fully independent suspension Frikar is powered by a pair of 25km/hr limited 250W e-bike motors. There is no mechanical link between the pedals &amp; wheels, rather you pedal input into one motor/generator and the energy is transferred by wire to motors at both rear wheels to propel you – just like the “<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/09/this-e-bike-system-has-no-chain-or-belt-and-it-recharges-as-you-pedal/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Bike By Wire</em></a>” systems we reported on from IAA Mobility. The result is classification as an e-bike, with a design e-assist range of 50-80km and featuring regenerative braking.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140013/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_evening-rendering.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140013/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_evening-rendering.jpg\" alt=\"PodBike Frikar x Storck enclosed e-bike pedelec e-velomobile,&nbsp;night rendering\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140013/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_evening-rendering.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140013/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_evening-rendering-297x167.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140013/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_evening-rendering-800x450.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140013/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_evening-rendering-120x68.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140013/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_evening-rendering-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140013/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_evening-rendering-1536x864.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The e-velomobile comes equipped with integrated headlights, taillights, operable turn signals &amp; extensive reflectors, plus outside side mirror. It also has a cup holder!, plus phone/tablet holder &amp; USB-charger inside, in addition to safety crumple zones and roll-over protection.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140009/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_rendering.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140009/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_rendering.jpg\" alt=\"PodBike Frikar x Storck enclosed e-bike pedelec e-velomobile,&nbsp;rendering\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140009/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_rendering.jpg 1800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140009/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_rendering-297x165.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140009/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_rendering-800x444.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140009/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_rendering-120x67.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140009/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_rendering-768x427.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140009/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_rendering-1536x853.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"></a></p><p>Interestingly, Podbike estimates that the aerodynamics of the shell should cancel out the additional weight &amp; rolling resistance penalties making it require an average of about 100W from the rider to pedal along at 30km/hr, what they say is the same as a conventional road bike.</p><p>Optional extras already in development include a manual windshield wiper for better visibility in foul weather, an internal fan for better airflow especially in hot weather, a child seat that sits behind the driver, a towbar hook to attach a conventional bike trailer, additional studded winter tires, or extra batteries for extended range.</p><h3>Podbike Frikar – Pricing, availability &amp; options</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140006/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_port.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140006/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_port.jpg\" alt=\"PodBike Frikar x Storck enclosed e-bike pedelec e-velomobile,&nbsp;angled port\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140006/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_port.jpg 1500w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140006/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_port-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140006/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_port-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140006/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_port-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140006/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_port-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"></a></p><p>This is always the trick with emerging technology… the Storck x Podbike Frikar e-velomobile isn’t ready quite yet – although pre-production Frikars are currently touring Norway &amp; Germany offering test drives. Podbike are taking pre-orders now with a 300€ deposit to lock in a reservation for one of the first Frikars. Final prices will start at 4995€, not including VAT, shipping or extra-add-ons.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140002/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_city-commuter.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140002/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_city-commuter.jpg\" alt=\"PodBike Frikar x Storck enclosed e-bike pedelec e-velomobile,&nbsp;city center\" width=\"1500\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140002/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_city-commuter.jpg 1500w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140002/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_city-commuter-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140002/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_city-commuter-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140002/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_city-commuter-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18140002/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_city-commuter-768x461.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"></a></p><p>Still, that sounds surprisingly affordable when most e-bikes top out over $5000€ for a premium commuter hardtail. Pretty much every performance full-suspension <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=eMTB\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">eMTB</a> we’ve seen starts around there, and often tops out over $10,000€.&nbsp; In fact, that’s also significantly cheaper than Storck’s recent smart, connected gravel/commuter<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/09/storck-porsche-cyklaer-collab-e-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> e-bike project Cyklaer</a>.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18135958/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_side-profile.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18135958/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_side-profile.jpg\" alt=\"PodBike Frikar x Storck enclosed e-bike pedelec e-velomobile,&nbsp;side\" width=\"1600\" height=\"882\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18135958/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_side-profile.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18135958/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_side-profile-297x164.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18135958/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_side-profile-800x441.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18135958/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_side-profile-120x66.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18135958/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_side-profile-768x423.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/18135958/PodBike-Frikar-x-Storck-enclosed-e-bike-pedelec-e-velomobile_side-profile-1536x847.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>Full-scale final production is expected to start in about 12 months. Storck &amp; Podbike say they already have over 3000 pre-orders, and are currently expecting to deliver the Frikar to those who place new pre-orders now sometime in 2023. Don’t throw away your car keys yet.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.podbike.com/\"><em>Podbike.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"697823b37fb253c56a584a914631c6bc46bf8b1a8ce0fa811855aa690ac5f0ae","category":"Cycling"}